main event: Observer observed 2 bright objects moving from the northwest to the southeast at 1:50 AM.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be round, bright, and silvery in color., The objects were visible for approximately 2 minutes., The observer estimated the size of the objects to be about the size of a basketball at arm's length., No radar detection was made for the objects., The observer reported the sighting 20 days after the actual observation.
witness description: The observer is a retired mail carrier, estimated to be 55-65 years old, living alone on a farm.
